<startElement uri="" localName="title" qName="title"/>
<characters>
Reported HTML presentation problems</characters>
<endElement uri="" localName="title" qName="title"/>
<characters>

</characters>
<startElement uri="" localName="para" qName="para"/>
<characters>
Some readers of these specifications have reported display problems with the presentation of the XPath addresses.  Reports typically indicate a mystery box-like character is being displayed after every oblique in the XPath address.  This is caused by the browser not correctly interpreting the Unicode character entity &#8203; for a zero-width space.  When the browser correctly recognizes this character, it is interpreted as a space for the purposes of line-breaking, but the zero-width of the character gives the appearance of the surrounding characters being adjacent (when it is properly interpreted).
</characters>
<endElement uri="" localName="para" qName="para"/>
<characters>
</characters>
<startElement uri="" localName="para" qName="para"/>
<characters>
To illustrate, the following is the sequence "</characters>
<startElement uri="" localName="literal" qName="literal"/>
<characters>A&#8203;B</characters>
<endElement uri="" localName="literal" qName="literal"/>
<characters>": "</characters>
<startElement uri="" localName="literal" qName="literal"/>
<characters>Aâ€‹B</characters>
<endElement uri="" localName="literal" qName="literal"/>
<characters>" (which should appear as "</characters>
<startElement uri="" localName="literal" qName="literal"/>
<characters>AB</characters>
<endElement uri="" localName="literal" qName="literal"/>
<characters>").</characters>
<endElement uri="" localName="para" qName="para"/>
<characters>

</characters>
